[{"location":"#GEMPIC.jl-Documentation-1","page":"GEMPIC.jl Documentation","title":"GEMPIC.jl Documentation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#","page":"GEMPIC.jl Documentation","title":"GEMPIC.jl Documentation","text":"Geometric ElectroMagnetic Particle-In-Cell Methods","category":"page"},{"location":"#","page":"GEMPIC.jl Documentation","title":"GEMPIC.jl Documentation","text":"A Julia implementation of the GEMPIC","category":"page"},{"location":"mesh/#Maxwell-solver-1","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"Maxwell solver","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"mesh/#","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"Maxwell solver","text":"Modules = [GEMPIC]\nPages   = [\"mesh.jl\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"mesh/#GEMPIC.get_x-Tuple{Mesh,Any}","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"GEMPIC.get_x","text":"Get position\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"mesh/#GEMPIC.get_cell_and_offset-Tuple{Mesh,Any}","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"GEMPIC.get_cell_and_offset","text":"Get cell and offset\n\nWe compute the cell indices where the particle is and its relative  normalized position inside the cell\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"low_level_bsplines/#Maxwell-solver-1","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"Maxwell solver","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"low_level_bsplines/#","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"Maxwell solver","text":"Modules = [GEMPIC]\nPages   = [\"low_level_bsplines.jl\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"low_level_bsplines/#GEMPIC.eval_uniform_periodic_spline_curve-Tuple{Int64,Array{Float64,1}}","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"GEMPIC.eval_uniform_periodic_spline_curve","text":"evaluniformperiodicsplinecurve( degree, scoef )\n\nEvaluate uniform periodic spline curve defined by coefficients scoef at  knots (which are the grid points) \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"low_level_bsplines/#GEMPIC.uniform_bsplines_eval_basis-Tuple{Int64,Float64}","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"GEMPIC.uniform_bsplines_eval_basis","text":"uniform_bsplines_eval_basis( spline_degree, normalized_offset, bspl )\n\nUNIFORM B-SPLINE FUNCTIONS\n\nEvaluate all non vanishing uniform B-Splines in unit cell.\n\nReturns an array with the values of the b-splines of the  requested degree, evaluated at a given cell offset. The cell size is normalized between 0 and 1, thus the offset given must be a number between 0 and 1.\n\nOutput: bspl(1d+1)= B_d(-(d+1)2+d+x)B_d(-(d+1)2+x)  with d=splinedegree and x=normalizedoffset where B_d=B_d-1*B_0 and B_0=1_-1212 and * is convolution the following code can be used for comparison with deboor\n\ndo i=-d,d+1\n    t(i+d+1)=real(i,8)\nend do\ncall bsplvb(t,d+1,1,normalized_offset,d+1,out)\n\nWe also have the property (from the symmetry of the B-spline)\n\nout(1d+1)= B_d(-(d+1)2+xx)B_d(-(d+1)2+d+xx) \n\nwhere xx=1-normalized_offset\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"splinepp/#Maxwell-solver-1","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"Maxwell solver","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"splinepp/#","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"Maxwell solver","text":"Modules = [GEMPIC]\nPages   = [\"splinepp.jl\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"splinepp/#GEMPIC.SplinePP","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"GEMPIC.SplinePP","text":"degree         : degree of 1d spline\npolycoeffs    : polycoeffs[i,j] coefficient of x^{deg+1-j} for ith B-spline function  size= (degree+1, degree+1)\npolycoeffsfp : poly_coeffs[i,j] coefficient of x^{deg+1-j} for ith B-spline function  size= (degree+1, degree+1)\nncells        : number of gridcells\nscratchb      : scratch data for bto_pp-converting\nscratchp      : scratch data for bto_pp-converting\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"splinepp/#GEMPIC.b_to_pp-Tuple{GEMPIC.SplinePP,Int64,Array{Float64,1}}","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"GEMPIC.b_to_pp","text":"Convert 1d spline in B form to spline in pp form with  periodic boundary conditions\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"splinepp/#GEMPIC.horner_1d-Tuple{Int64,Any,Float64,Int64}","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"GEMPIC.horner_1d","text":"Perform a 1d hornerschema on the pp_coeffs at index\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"splinepp/#GEMPIC.horner_primitive_1d-Tuple{Array{Float64,1},Any,Any,Any}","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"GEMPIC.horner_primitive_1d","text":"Perform a 1d hornerschema on the pp_coeffs evaluate at x\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_mesh_coupling/#Particle-Mesh-coupling-1","page":"Particle-Mesh coupling","title":"Particle-Mesh coupling","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"particle_mesh_coupling/#","page":"Particle-Mesh coupling","title":"Particle-Mesh coupling","text":"Modules = [GEMPIC]\nPages   = [\"particle_mesh_coupling.jl\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"particle_mesh_coupling/#GEMPIC.ParticleMeshCoupling","page":"Particle-Mesh coupling","title":"GEMPIC.ParticleMeshCoupling","text":"Kernel smoother with splines of arbitrary degree placed on a uniform mesh. Spline with index i starts at point i\n\nValue of grid spacing along both directions.\nDefinition of the domain: domain(1:2) = x1min, x1max\nNumber of particles of underlying PIC method (processor local)\nDegree of smoothing kernel spline\nNumber of intervals where spline non zero (spline_degree + 1)\nScaling factor depending on whether Galerkin or collocation\nNumber of quadrature points\nscratch data for spline evaluation\nmore scratch data for spline evaluation\nquadrature weights and points\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"particle_mesh_coupling/#GEMPIC.add_charge!-Tuple{Array{Float64,1},ParticleMeshCoupling,Array{Float64,1},Float64}","page":"Particle-Mesh coupling","title":"GEMPIC.add_charge!","text":"Add charge of one particle\n\np              : kernel smoother object\nposition       : Position of the particle\nmarker_charge  : Particle weights time charge\nrho_dofs       : Coefficient vector of the charge distribution\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_mesh_coupling/#GEMPIC.add_charge_pp!-Tuple{Array{Float64,1},Any,Any,Any}","page":"Particle-Mesh coupling","title":"GEMPIC.add_charge_pp!","text":"Add charge of one particle\n\np             : kernel smoother object\nposition      : Position of the particle\nmarker_charge : Particle weights time charge\nrho_dofs      : Coefficient vector of the charge distribution\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_mesh_coupling/#GEMPIC.add_current_update_v!-Tuple{AbstractArray,ParticleMeshCoupling,Array{Float64,1},Array{Float64,1},Float64,Float64,Array{Float64,1},Array{Float64,1}}","page":"Particle-Mesh coupling","title":"GEMPIC.add_current_update_v!","text":"Add current for one particle and update v (according to H_p1 part in Hamiltonian splitting)\n\nRead out particle position and velocity\nCompute index_old, the index of the last DoF on the grid the \n\nparticle contributes to, and r_old, its position (normalized to cell size one).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_mesh_coupling/#GEMPIC.add_current_update_v_pp!-Tuple{AbstractArray,ParticleMeshCoupling,Any,Any,Any,Any,Any,Any}","page":"Particle-Mesh coupling","title":"GEMPIC.add_current_update_v_pp!","text":"Add current for one particle and update v  (according to H_p1 part in Hamiltonian splitting)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_mesh_coupling/#GEMPIC.evaluate-Tuple{ParticleMeshCoupling,Float64,Array{Float64,1}}","page":"Particle-Mesh coupling","title":"GEMPIC.evaluate","text":"Evaluate field at position\n\np : Kernel smoother object \nposition(p.dim) : Position of the particle\nfield_dofs(p.n_dofs) : Coefficient vector for the field DoFs\nfield_value : Value(s) of the electric fields at given position\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_mesh_coupling/#GEMPIC.evaluate_pp-Tuple{ParticleMeshCoupling,Float64,Array{Float64,2}}","page":"Particle-Mesh coupling","title":"GEMPIC.evaluate_pp","text":"Evaluate field at position using horner scheme\n\np : Kernel smoother object \nposition(p.dim) : Position of the particle\nfield_dofs_pp[:,:] : Degrees of freedom in kernel representation.\nfield_value : Value(s) of the electric fields at given position\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_mesh_coupling/#GEMPIC.update_jv!-Tuple{AbstractArray,ParticleMeshCoupling,Float64,Float64,Int64,Float64,Float64,Float64,Float64,Array{Float64,1}}","page":"Particle-Mesh coupling","title":"GEMPIC.update_jv!","text":"Helper function for \u0007 addcurrentupdate_v.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_mesh_coupling/#GEMPIC.update_jv_pp!-Tuple{AbstractArray,ParticleMeshCoupling,Float64,Float64,Int64,Float64,Float64,Float64,Array{Float64,1}}","page":"Particle-Mesh coupling","title":"GEMPIC.update_jv_pp!","text":"Helper function for \u0007 addcurrentupdate_v.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_group/#Particle-group-1","page":"Particle group","title":"Particle group","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"particle_group/#","page":"Particle group","title":"Particle group","text":"Modules = [GEMPIC]\nPages   = [\"particle_group.jl\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"particle_group/#GEMPIC.get_v-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{D}, Tuple{ParticleGroup{D,V},Any}} where V where D","page":"Particle group","title":"GEMPIC.get_v","text":"Get velocities\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_group/#GEMPIC.get_x-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{D}, Tuple{ParticleGroup{D,V},Any}} where V where D","page":"Particle group","title":"GEMPIC.get_x","text":"Get position\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_group/#GEMPIC.get_charge-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{D}, Tuple{ParticleGroup{D,V},Any}} where V where D","page":"Particle group","title":"GEMPIC.get_charge","text":"Get charge of particle (q * particle_weight)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_group/#GEMPIC.get_mass-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{D}, Tuple{ParticleGroup{D,V},Any}} where V where D","page":"Particle group","title":"GEMPIC.get_mass","text":"Get mass of particle (m * particle_weight)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_group/#GEMPIC.get_weights-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{D}, Tuple{ParticleGroup{D,V},Any}} where V where D","page":"Particle group","title":"GEMPIC.get_weights","text":"Get particle weights\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_group/#GEMPIC.set_common_weight-Tuple{GEMPIC.AbstractParticleGroup,Any}","page":"Particle group","title":"GEMPIC.set_common_weight","text":"Set the common weight\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_group/#GEMPIC.set_v-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{D}, Tuple{ParticleGroup{D,V},Any,Array{Float64,1}}} where V where D","page":"Particle group","title":"GEMPIC.set_v","text":"Set velocity of particle @ i\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_group/#GEMPIC.set_v-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{D}, Tuple{ParticleGroup{D,V},Any,Float64}} where V where D","page":"Particle group","title":"GEMPIC.set_v","text":"Set velocity of particle @ i\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_group/#GEMPIC.set_weights-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{D}, Tuple{ParticleGroup{D,V},Any,Array{Float64,1}}} where V where D","page":"Particle group","title":"GEMPIC.set_weights","text":"Set weights of particle @ i\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_group/#GEMPIC.set_weights-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{D}, Tuple{ParticleGroup{D,V},Any,Float64}} where V where D","page":"Particle group","title":"GEMPIC.set_weights","text":"Set weights of particle @ i\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_group/#GEMPIC.set_x-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{D}, Tuple{ParticleGroup{D,V},Any,Array{Float64,1}}} where V where D","page":"Particle group","title":"GEMPIC.set_x","text":"Set position of particle @ i\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_group/#GEMPIC.set_x-Union{Tuple{V}, Tuple{D}, Tuple{ParticleGroup{D,V},Any,Float64}} where V where D","page":"Particle group","title":"GEMPIC.set_x","text":"Set position of particle @ i\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_sampling/#Particle-sampling-1","page":"Particle sampling","title":"Particle sampling","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"particle_sampling/#","page":"Particle sampling","title":"Particle sampling","text":"Modules = [GEMPIC]\nPages   = [\"particle_sampling.jl\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"particle_sampling/#GEMPIC.ParticleSampler","page":"Particle sampling","title":"GEMPIC.ParticleSampler","text":"Particle initializer class with various functions to initialize a particle.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"particle_sampling/#GEMPIC.sample-Tuple{ParticleSampler,ParticleGroup{1,2},VlasovBase.CosGaussian,Mesh}","page":"Particle sampling","title":"GEMPIC.sample","text":"Sample from distribution defined by \u0007 params\n\nxmin : lower bound of the domain\nLx   : length of the domain.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_sampling/#GEMPIC.sample_all-NTuple{4,Any}","page":"Particle sampling","title":"GEMPIC.sample_all","text":"Helper function for pure sampling\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"particle_sampling/#GEMPIC.sample_sym-NTuple{4,Any}","page":"Particle sampling","title":"GEMPIC.sample_sym","text":"Helper function for antithetic sampling in 1d2v\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"maxwell_solver/#Maxwell-solver-1","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"Maxwell solver","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"maxwell_solver/#","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"Maxwell solver","text":"Modules = [GEMPIC]\nPages   = [\"maxwell_1d_fem.jl\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"maxwell_solver/#GEMPIC.Maxwell1DFEM","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"GEMPIC.Maxwell1DFEM","text":"maxwell_solver = MaxwellFEM1D( domain, ncells, degree )\n\n1D Maxwell spline finite element solver on a periodic grid\n\nLx                   : length of Periodic domain\ndelta_x              : cell size\nn_dofs               : number of cells (and grid points)\nsdeg0              : spline degree 0-forms\nsdeg1              : spline degree 1-forms\nmass_0               : coefficients of 0-form mass matrix\nmass_1               : coefficients of 1-form mass matrix\neig_mass0            : eigenvalues of circulant 0-form mass matrix\neig_mass1            : eigenvalues of circulant 1-form mass matrix\neigweakampere      : eigenvalues of circulant update matrix for Ampere\neigweakpoisson     : eigenvalues of circulant update matrix for Poisson\nplan_fw              : fft plan (forward)\nplan_bw              : fft plan (backward)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"maxwell_solver/#GEMPIC.compute_b_from_e!-Tuple{Array{Float64,1},Maxwell1DFEM,Float64,Array{Float64,1}}","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"GEMPIC.compute_b_from_e!","text":"Compute Bz from Ey using strong 1D Faraday equation for spline coefficients\n\nB_z^new(x_j) = B_z^old(x_j) - fracDelta tDelta x (E_y(x_j) - E_y(x_j-1)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"maxwell_solver/#GEMPIC.compute_e_from_b!-Tuple{Array{Float64,1},Maxwell1DFEM,Float64,Array{Float64,1}}","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"GEMPIC.compute_e_from_b!","text":"compute Ey from Bz using weak Ampere formulation \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"maxwell_solver/#GEMPIC.compute_e_from_j!-Tuple{Array{Float64,1},Maxwell1DFEM,Array{Float64,1},Int64}","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"GEMPIC.compute_e_from_j!","text":"Compute E_i from j_i integrated over the time interval using weak Ampere formulation\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"maxwell_solver/#GEMPIC.compute_rhs_from_function!-Tuple{Array{Float64,1},Maxwell1DFEM,Function,Int64}","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"GEMPIC.compute_rhs_from_function!","text":"computerhsfromfunction(self, func, degree, coefsdofs)\n\nCompute the FEM right-hand-side for a given function f and periodic splines of given degree.\n\nIts components are int f N_i dx where N_i is the B-spline starting at x_i. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"maxwell_solver/#GEMPIC.l2norm_squared-Tuple{Any,Any,Any}","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"GEMPIC.l2norm_squared","text":"Compute square of the L2norm\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"maxwell_solver/#GEMPIC.l2projection!-Tuple{Array{Float64,1},Maxwell1DFEM,Function,Int64}","page":"Maxwell solver","title":"GEMPIC.l2projection!","text":"Compute the L2 projection of a given function f on periodic splines  of given degree\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"hamiltonian_splitting/#Hamiltonian-splitting-1","page":"Hamiltonian splitting","title":"Hamiltonian splitting","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"hamiltonian_splitting/#","page":"Hamiltonian splitting","title":"Hamiltonian splitting","text":"Modules = [GEMPIC]\nPages   = [\"hamiltonian_splitting.jl\"]","category":"page"},{"location":"hamiltonian_splitting/#GEMPIC.HamiltonianSplitting","page":"Hamiltonian splitting","title":"GEMPIC.HamiltonianSplitting","text":"Hamiltonian splitting type for Vlasov-Maxwell\n\nIntegral over the spline function on each interval (order p+1)\nIntegral over the spline function on each interval (order p)\n\n!< DoFs describing the two components of the electric field DoFs describing the magnetic field DoFs for kernel representation of current density.  MPI-processor local part of one component of \u0007 j_dofs\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"hamiltonian_splitting/#GEMPIC.operatorHB-Tuple{Any,Any}","page":"Hamiltonian splitting","title":"GEMPIC.operatorHB","text":"Push HB: Equations to be solved ``Vnew = V_old``\n\nbegineqnarray\npartial_t E_1 = 0  -  E_1new = E_1old \npartial_t E_2 = - partial_x_1 B  -  E_2new = E_2old-dt*partial_x_1 B \npartial_t B = 0  -  B_new = B_old \nendeqnarray\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"hamiltonian_splitting/#GEMPIC.operatorHE-Tuple{HamiltonianSplitting,Any}","page":"Hamiltonian splitting","title":"GEMPIC.operatorHE","text":"Push H_E: Equations to be solved\n\nbegineqnarray\npartial_t f + E_1 partial_v_1 f + E_2 partial_v_2 f = 0 - V_new = V_old + dt * E \npartial_t E_1 = 0 - E_1new = E_1old \npartial_t E_2 = 0 - E_2new = E_2old \npartial_t B + partial_x_1 E_2 = 0 - B_new = B_old - dt partial_x_1 E_2\nendeqnarray\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"hamiltonian_splitting/#GEMPIC.operatorHp1-Tuple{HamiltonianSplitting,Float64}","page":"Hamiltonian splitting","title":"GEMPIC.operatorHp1","text":"begineqnarray\npartial_t f + v_1 partial_x_1 f = 0  -   X_new = X_old + dt V_1 \nV_new2 = V_old2 + int_0 h V_old1 B_old  \npartial_t E_1 = - int v_1 f(tx_1 v) dv  -  E_1new = E_1old - \nint int v_1 f(tx_1+s v_1v) dv ds   \npartial_t E_2 = 0  -  E_2new = E_2old \npartial_t B = 0  =  B_new = B_old \nendeqnarray\n\nHere we have to accumulate j and integrate over the time interval. At each k=1n_grid, we have for s in 0dt j_k(s) =  sum_i=1N_p q_i N((x_k+sv_1k-x_i)h) v_k, where h is the grid spacing and N the normalized B-spline  In order to accumulate the integrated j, we normalize the values of  x to the grid spacing,      calling them y, we have\n\n j_k(s) = sum_i=1N_p q_i N(y_k+fracsh v_1k-y_i) v_k\n\nNow, we want the integral\n\nint_0dt j_k(s) d s = sum_i=1^N_p q_i v_k \nint_0dt N(y_k+fracsh v_1k-y_i) ds \n=  sum_i=1^N_p q_i v_k  int_0^dt  N(y_k + w v_1k-y_i) dw\n\nFor each particle compute the index of the first DoF on the grid it contributes  to and its position (normalized to cell size one). Note: j_dofs  does not hold the values for j itself but for the integrated j.\n\nThen update particle position:   X_new = X_old + dt * V\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"hamiltonian_splitting/#GEMPIC.operatorHp2-Tuple{Any,Any}","page":"Hamiltonian splitting","title":"GEMPIC.operatorHp2","text":"Push Hp2: Equations to solve are\n\nbegineqnarray X_new  =  X_old  \nV_new1 = V_old1 + int_0 h V_old2 B_old  \npartial_t E_1 = 0  -  E_1new = E_1old  \npartial_t E_2 = - int v_2 f(tx_1 v) dv  -   \nE_2new = E_2old - int int v_2 f(tx_1 + s v_1v) dv ds \npartial_t B = 0 = B_new = B_old  \nendeqnarray\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"hamiltonian_splitting/#GEMPIC.lie_splitting-Tuple{HamiltonianSplitting,Float64,Int64}","page":"Hamiltonian splitting","title":"GEMPIC.lie_splitting","text":"Lie splitting\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"hamiltonian_splitting/#GEMPIC.lie_splitting_back-Tuple{HamiltonianSplitting,Float64,Int64}","page":"Hamiltonian splitting","title":"GEMPIC.lie_splitting_back","text":"Lie splitting (oposite ordering)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"hamiltonian_splitting/#GEMPIC.strang_splitting-Tuple{HamiltonianSplitting,Float64,Int64}","page":"Hamiltonian splitting","title":"GEMPIC.strang_splitting","text":"Strang splitting\n\ntime splitting object \ntime step\nnumber of time steps\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"contents/#Contents-1","page":"Contents","title":"Contents","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"contents/#","page":"Contents","title":"Contents","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"contents/#Index-1","page":"Contents","title":"Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"contents/#","page":"Contents","title":"Contents","text":"","category":"page"}]
